This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing (NLP) and the use of neural language models (NLMs) for generating fake online reviews. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning classifiers for filtering out undesired sentiment, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact on online shopping, which could be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of NLMs and machine learning also falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
